2026-02-21 15:00:25 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "Travel Planner: Create day-by-day itinerary with activities, hotel options (budget/mid/luxury + prices), and budget breakdown (accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total).", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f$600)  \n\n| Item | Budget (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\n|------|------------|--------------|------------|\n| **Accommodation** (2 nights) | 2,000\u202f\u2013\u202f4,000 | 6,000\u202f\u2013\u202f10,000 | 15,000\u202f\u2013\u202f25,000 |\n| **Food & Drinks** (2\u202fdays) | 2,000\u202f\u2013\u202f3,000 | 4,000\u202f\u2013\u202f6,000 | 8,000\u202f\u2013\u202f12,000 |\n| **Local Transport** (airport\u2011to\u2011hotel, day\u2011to\u2011day) | 1,200\u202f\u2013\u202f1,800 | 2,000\u202f\u2013\u202f3,000 | 4,000\u202f\u2013\u202f6,000 |\n| **Attractions / Activities** | 1,500\u202f\u2013\u202f2,500 | 3,000\u202f\u2013\u202f5,000 | 6,000\u202f\u2013\u202f9,000 |\n| **Misc. (souvenirs, tips, entry fees)** | 500\u202f\u2013\u202f800 | 800\u202f\u2013\u202f1,200 | 1,200\u202f\u2013\u202f2,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b97,200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b912,100** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b915,800\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b925,200** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b934,200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b953,800** |\n\n> **Bottom line:** Even the \u201cbudget\u201d version stays well under your \u20b950,000 ceiling, leaving plenty of room for extra splurges (water sports, fine\u2011dining, spa, etc.). Below is a full day\u2011by\u2011day plan with three hotel tiers and cost estimates for each component.\n\n---\n\n## DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### **Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival, North Goa Beaches & Nightlife**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Cost |\n|------|----------|------------------------|\n| **08:00 \u2013 09:30** | **Arrival & Transfer** | Fly into Dabolim (GOI). Pre\u2011book a **shared airport shuttle** (\u20b9300\u2011\u20b9400 per person) or a **private taxi** (\u20b91,200\u2011\u20b91,500). |\n| **09:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Check\u2011in & Freshen up** | Drop bags at hotel (see options below). |\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beach** | Sunbathe, swim, optional water\u2011sport (parasailing \u20b91,200). |\n| **12:30 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch** | Beach shacks \u2013 Goan fish thali (\u20b9250\u2011\u20b9350). |\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Entry free; small parking fee \u20b930. |\n| **15:30 \u2013 17:00** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Sat\u2011only) | Souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. Budget \u20b9500\u2011\u20b9800. |\n| **17:00 \u2013 18:30** | **Sunset at Chapora Fort** | Great photo spot; free. |\n| **19:00 \u2013 21:00** | **Dinner** | **Budget:** Thali at \u201cMum\u2019s Kitchen\u201d (\u20b9300). **Mid:** \u201cBritto\u2019s\u201d on Baga (\u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200). **Luxury:** \u201cThalassa\u201d (\u20b92,000\u2011\u20b93,000). |\n| **21:30 \u2013 Late** | **Nightlife** | **Budget:** \u201cClub Cabana\u201d entry \u20b9500 (incl. 1 drink). **Mid:** \u201cCaf\u00e9 Mambo\u201d (\u20b9800). **Luxury:** \u201cTito\u2019s\u201d VIP table (\u20b92,500). |\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel** | Use auto\u2011rickshaw (\u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250) or hotel\u2011arranged shuttle. |\n\n---\n\n### **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Culture & Relaxation**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Cost |\n|------|----------|------------------------|\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (included in mid\u2011lux) or local caf\u00e9 (\u20b9150\u2011\u20b9250). |\n| **08:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Old Goa Churches** (Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus & Se\u202fCathedral) | Entry free; guide (optional) \u20b9300\u2011\u20b9500. |\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:00** | **Spice Plantation Tour** (Sahakari or Tropical) | Guided tour + lunch, \u20b91,200\u2011\u20b91,500 per person. |\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch** | Included in plantation tour (Goan thali). |\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:30** | **Colva / Palolem Beach** | Relax, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b91,500). |\n| **15:30 \u2013 16:30** | **Coffee break** | Beachside caf\u00e9, coconut water & snack (\u20b9200). |\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:00** | **Shopping / Souvenirs** | Local markets (Panjim, Mapusa). |\n| **18:30 \u2013 20:00** | **Dinner** | **Budget:** \u201cMartin\u2019s Corner\u201d (\u20b9500\u2011\u20b9800). **Mid:** \u201cMartin\u2019s\u201d with seafood platter (\u20b91,200). **Luxury:** \u201cThe Fisherman\u2019s Wharf\u201d (\u20b92,500\u2011\u20b93,500). |\n| **20:30** | **Transfer to Airport** | Pre\u2011book taxi (\u20b91,200\u2011\u20b91,500) or shuttle. |\n| **22:00** | **Departure** | Fly out of Dabolim. |\n\n---\n\n## HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Tier | Property (North Goa) | Approx. Nightly Rate (\u20b9) | Amenities | Why It Fits |\n|------|----------------------|--------------------------|-----------|-------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Guesthouse** (Calangute) | 1,000\u202f\u2013\u202f1,500 | Clean rooms, free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop, near beach | Ideal for backpackers; easy beach access |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim) | 3,000\u202f\u2013\u202f4,500 | Pool, sea\u2011view rooms, breakfast, 24\u2011hr desk | Comfortable, good location for both north & south trips |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | 12,000\u202f\u2013\u202f15,000 | Private beach, spa, multiple restaurants, pool | Premium experience, perfect for a splurge night |\n\n> **Tip:** Book 2\u2011night stays on a site like **MakeMyTrip** or **Booking.com** and use the \u201cpay\u2011later\u201d option if you prefer to keep cash on hand for activities.\n\n### Sample Cost Breakdown (Mid\u2011range)\n\n| Category | Cost (\u20b9) |\n|----------|----------|\n| **Accommodation** (2 nights @ \u20b93,500) | 7,000 |\n| **Food & Drinks** (average \u20b91,200/day) | 2,400 |\n| **Transport** (airport\u2011taxi + 2\u2011day auto/rental) | 2,500 |\n| **Attractions** (parasailing, spice tour, dolphin\u2011watch) | 3,500 |\n| **Miscellaneous** (souvenirs, tips) | 1,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b916,400** |\n\nEven with a few upgrades (luxury hotel + extra water\u2011sports), you\u2019ll stay comfortably under **\u20b950,000**.\n\n---\n\n## QUICK\u2011LOOK BUDGET CHEAT\u2011SHEET  \n\n| Expense | Budget (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\n|---------|------------|--------------|------------|\n| **Accommodation** (2\u202fnights) | 2,000\u202f\u2013\u202f4,000 | 6,000\u202f\u2013\u202f10,000 | 15,000\u202f\u2013\u202f25,000 |\n| **Food** | 2,000\u202f\u2013\u202f3,000 | 4,000\u202f\u2013\u202f6,000 | 8,000\u202f\u2013\u202f12,000 |\n| **Transport** | 1,200\u202f\u2013\u202f1,800 | 2,000\u202f\u2013\u202f3,000 | 4,000\u202f\u2013\u202f6,000 |\n| **Activities** | 1,500\u202f\u2013\u202f2,500 | 3,000\u202f\u2013\u202f5,000 | 6,000\u202f\u2013\u202f9,000 |\n| **Misc.** | 500\u202f\u2013\u202f800 | 800\u202f\u2013\u202f1,200 | 1,200\u202f\u2013\u202f2,000 |\n| **Grand Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b97,200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b912,100** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b915,800\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b925,200** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b934,200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b953,800** |\n\n---\n\n## PRACTICAL TIPS  \n\n1. **Travel Light** \u2013 A small backpack + a day\u2011pack is enough; most beach shacks have lockers.  \n2. **Cash & Cards** \u2013 Carry \u20b95,000\u2011\u20b97,000 in cash for small vendors; most hotels & restaurants accept cards.  \n3. **Sun Protection** \u2013 Sunscreen (\u20b9300\u2011\u20b9500), hat, and sunglasses are a must.  \n4. **Local SIM** \u2013 Buy a prepaid Jio/Idea plan (\u20b9200 for 2\u202fGB data) at the airport.  \n5. **Safety** \u2013 Keep an eye on your belongings on crowded beaches; avoid isolated spots after dark.  \n6. **Timing** \u2013 Peak tourist season (Nov\u2011Feb) is busy; book hotels & activities **at least 2\u202fweeks** in advance.  \n\n---\n\n### Ready to Book?  \n\n- **Flights**: Look for budget carriers (IndiGo, SpiceJet) \u2013 round\u2011trip from major Indian metros \u2248\u202f\u20b96,000\u2011\u20b99,000.  \n- **Hotel**: Use the links below (they have \u201cinstant\u2011confirm\u201d rates).  \n- **Activities**: Pre\u2011book the spice\u2011plantation tour and any water\u2011sports via **Klook** or **Viator** for guaranteed slots.  \n\nEnjoy your Goa adventure \u2013 sun, sea, spice, and a dash of nightlife, all within your \u20b950k budget! \ud83c\udf1e\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83c\udf64"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py] line number [13] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "## What the error means  \n\n```\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\nWhen the `GoogleMap.py` module raised `HolidayAgentException`, the constructor of that exception class was called **without** the argument it expects (`error_detail`).  \nPython therefore aborts with a `TypeError` before your own error\u2011handling code can run.\n\n### Typical call\u2011stack (simplified)\n\n```text\nFile \"GoogleMap.py\", line 13, in <module>\n    raise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch map data\")\n```\n\nIf `HolidayAgentException` is defined like this:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_code: int, error_detail: str):\n        self.error_code = error_code\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n        super().__init__(f\"[{error_code}] {error_detail}\")\n```\n\n\u2026 then the raise statement above is missing the required `error_detail` (and also the `error_code`).  \nHence the interpreter complains that one positional argument is missing.\n\n---\n\n## Step\u2011by\u2011step fix\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Locate the exception class definition  \n\nOpen the file where `HolidayAgentException` is declared (most likely `HolidayAgentException.py` or inside a common `exceptions.py` module).\n\n```python\n# Example \u2013 current (problematic) definition\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_code: int, error_detail: str):\n        self.error_code = error_code\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n        super().__init__(f\"[{error_code}] {error_detail}\")\n```\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Decide on the desired signature  \n\nYou have two options:\n\n| Option | When to use | How to change |\n|--------|-------------|---------------|\n| **A. Keep both arguments (error_code, error_detail)** | You want a structured error (code\u202f+\u202fmessage). | Every `raise HolidayAgentException(...)` must supply **both** arguments. |\n| **B. Make `error_detail` optional (or drop `error_code`)** | Simpler usage throughout the codebase, or you only need a message. | Modify `__init__` to give default values. |\n\n#### Option\u202fA \u2013 Update every raise site  \n\n```python\n# In GoogleMap.py line 13 (example)\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    error_code=1001,\n    error_detail=\"Failed to fetch map data from Google Maps API\"\n)\n```\n\nDo the same for any other place that raises the exception.\n\n#### Option\u202fB \u2013 Make arguments optional  \n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_code: int = 0, error_detail: str = \"Unknown error\"):\n        self.error_code = error_code\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n        # Build a readable message for the base Exception\n        message = f\"[{error_code}] {error_detail}\" if error_code else error_detail\n        super().__init__(message)\n```\n\nNow you can raise it with just a message:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(error_detail=\"Failed to fetch map data\")\n# or even\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch map data\")   # positional arg maps to error_code, so better use keyword\n```\n\n> **Tip:** Using keyword arguments (`error_detail=`) makes the intent crystal\u2011clear and avoids ordering mistakes.\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Verify imports  \n\nMake sure the module that defines `HolidayAgentException` is correctly imported in `GoogleMap.py`:\n\n```python\n# At the top of GoogleMap.py\nfrom ..exceptions import HolidayAgentException   # adjust the relative path as needed\n```\n\nIf the import path is wrong, Python may be pulling in a *different* class with a different signature, which also triggers the same error.\n\n### 4\ufe0f\u20e3 Run a quick sanity test  \n\nCreate a tiny script in the same virtual environment:\n\n```python\nfrom path.to.HolidayAgentException import HolidayAgentException\n\ntry:\n    raise HolidayAgentException(error_detail=\"test\")\nexcept HolidayAgentException as e:\n    print(\"Caught:\", e)\n```\n\nIf it prints `Caught: test` (or `[0] test` depending on your implementation), the exception class works.\n\n### 5\ufe0f\u20e3 Re\u2011run your original workflow  \n\nNow execute the part of your travel\u2011assistant that calls `GoogleMap.py`. The error should be gone, and you\u2019ll either get the expected map data or a more informative custom exception message.\n\n---\n\n## Quick checklist for you\n\n| \u2705 | Action |\n|---|--------|\n| **1** | Open the file where `HolidayAgentException` is defined. |\n| **2** | Decide whether you want a mandatory `error_code` + `error_detail` **or** optional arguments. |\n| **3** | Adjust the `__init__` signature accordingly (add defaults if you want them optional). |\n| **4** | Update every `raise HolidayAgentException(...)` call to match the new signature (use keyword arguments). |\n| **5** | Verify the import statement in `GoogleMap.py`. |\n| **6** | Run a tiny test script to confirm the exception works. |\n| **7** | Re\u2011run the full travel\u2011assistant flow. |\n\n---\n\n## Example \u2013 Full corrected snippet\n\n```python\n# \u2500\u2500 exceptions.py \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent suite.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, error_code: int = 0, error_detail: str = \"Unknown error\"):\n        self.error_code = error_code\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n        # Build a friendly message for the base Exception\n        msg = f\"[{error_code}] {error_detail}\" if error_code else error_detail\n        super().__init__(msg)\n\n\n# \u2500\u2500 GoogleMap.py \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nfrom path.to.exceptions import HolidayAgentException\nimport requests\n\ndef fetch_map(lat: float, lng: float) -> dict:\n    try:\n        resp = requests.get(\n            \"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap\",\n            params={\"center\": f\"{lat},{lng}\", \"zoom\": 12, \"size\": \"600x400\", \"key\": API_KEY},\n            timeout=10,\n        )\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return resp.json()\n    except requests.RequestException as exc:\n        # Now we pass both arguments (or just the message if you kept error_code optional)\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\n            error_code=2001,\n            error_detail=f\"Google Maps request failed: {exc}\"\n        ) from exc\n```\n\nWith the above changes, the `HolidayAgentException` will be instantiated correctly, and the original `requests` error will be wrapped in a clear, domain\u2011specific exception.\n\n---\n\n### Need more help?\n\n* If you\u2019re still seeing the same traceback, paste the **exact line** that raises the exception and the **current definition** of `HolidayAgentException` \u2013 I can pinpoint the mismatch.\n* If you prefer to keep the original signature (no defaults) but only have a few raise sites, just add the missing argument(s) at those sites.\n\nHappy debugging, and may your next map lookup be error\u2011free! \ud83d\ude80\ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py] line number [13] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "## TL;DR  \nThe traceback tells us that **`HolidayAgentException` is being instantiated without the required `error_detail` argument** (and possibly without `error_code` as well).  \nFix it by either  \n\n1. **Supplying the missing argument(s) wherever the exception is raised**, **or**  \n2. **Changing the exception class definition to make the argument optional (or give it a default value).**  \n\nBelow is a complete, step\u2011by\u2011step guide that walks you through locating the problem, fixing the code, and verifying that the error is gone.\n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Understand the exact failure\n\n```\nFile \"C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py\", line 13, in <module>\n    raise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch map data\")\nTypeError: HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\n*`HolidayAgentException`* expects **at least two positional arguments** (most likely `error_code` and `error_detail`).  \nBecause the raise statement only passes one argument (or none), Python raises a `TypeError` before your custom exception can 